r, people there have not been a passive and pliable audience for these efforts. They have brought their skills as "anarchic listeners" to these encounters, advancing political agendas of their own.To understand political life in the Yopno Valley, we need to look beyond what people say to the practices that lie on the other side of the word. This, Slotta suggests, is also true well beyond the bounds of the Yopno Valley.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAnarchismzPapua New Guinea. 0aListeningxPolitical aspectszPapua New Guinea. 0aListeningxSocial aspectszPapua New Guinea. 4aANTHROPOLOGY. 4aLANGUAGE ARTS & LINGUISTICS. 4aSOCIOLOGY & SOCIAL SCIENCE. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  apolitical listening, anarchy in Papua New Guinea, ethnography of listening, social change in Papua New Guinea, Yopno valley, political communication, anarchic communities, anarchic politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150177002940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501770029423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501770029/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_SN